author: Eric Snider
title: Sarasota Bradenton Airport adds seasonal Canadian carrier
text:
Norm Betts for Bloomberg News WestJet becomes SRQ's sixth carrier. Maybe itâ€™s the winters. Uh, ya think? Sarasota Bradenton International Airport (SRQ) has added a new seasonal carrier to its roster of airlines. Beginning Dec. 18, WestJet , a low-cost carrier based in Calgary, Canada, will offer one nonstop flight per day on Fridays and Sundays between SRQ and Toronto Pearson International Airport. The service will run through April 29, 2016, and use 136-seat Boeing 737-700 aircraft. The addition of WestJet brings the total number of airlines operating at SRQ to six. The Friday and Sunday flights will depart Toronto at 8:05 a.m. and arrive at 11:06 a.m., The SRQ-to-Toronto leg leaves at 11:55 a.m. and arrives at 2:39 p.m.
